org.jimmutable.core.fields

Class FieldArrayList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jimmutable.core.fields.FieldCollection<E>
      • org.jimmutable.core.fields.FieldList<E>
        • org.jimmutable.core.fields.FieldArrayList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of elements in this list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>, Field

    public final class FieldArrayList<E>
extends FieldList<E>
    An implementation of a ArrayList that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable). In other words, a wrapper for a ArrayList that implements Field.

    Note: ArrayList, and consequently FieldArrayList is not thread safe. This is generally not a concern once "frozen" but if the construction process is multi-threaded, consider FieldCopyOnWriteArrayList.

    In the standard case (construction in one thread), FieldArrayList will work well.

    Author:
    Jim Kane
    See Also:
    FieldList
